Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 4 YEARS consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 years with credit for  3 days time served. Defendant shall serve 2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION. The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

 *Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge.
 *Court ordered defendant to pay the restitution, costs and disbursements from up to 25% of prison funds.    Court ordered DOC to collect any monetary amounts provided in Wis. Stats. section 973.05(4)(b), 303.01(8), and 973.20 while the defendant is in their control.

The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute.  Copy of form CR234 provided to defendant. 

Court orders $600.00 fine plus all mandatory costs, fees and surcharges (including DNA surcharge) are due by the end of probation/extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 

Court ordered defendant's operating privileges revoked for 32 months with the mandatory reinstatement fee.  

Defendant's operating privilege for operation of Class D vehicles is restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an ignition interlock device; and each motor vehicle for which the defendant's name appears on the vehicle's certificate of title or registration must be equipped with an ignition interlock device beginning on the date the department issues any license and for a period of  32 months  thereafter.

The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of 3 years.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
-  6 months condition time with Huber for work;
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician and for only as long as deemed medically necessary for defendant's physical or mental health;
-  No driving while on medication;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Parenting classes
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
-  Drivers assesment and safety plan.

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department. 

